{"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModelBuilder"],"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModel"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/init(_:name:)-4pup0","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/init(_:name:)-55gex"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(_:inputs:_:streamContext:)-101bg","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(_:inputs:_:streamContext:)-4i10p","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(inputs:_:streamContext:)-4tnis","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(inputs:_:streamContext:)-8pae9","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(_:inputs:isEager:)-1lsvw","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(_:inputs:isEager:)-8ge5z","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(inputs:isEager:)-4kat6","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(inputs:isEager:)-4yweq"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A model builder is a more generic type of model. A model can be quite static,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thus, you have to be quite careful to have a model work with dynamic inputs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You cannot use reshape, or anything that can generate fixed tensor outputs from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a fixed inputs."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/nnc\/modelbuilder"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ModelBuilder","externalID":"s:3NNC12ModelBuilderC","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"NNC"}],"role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["Linux"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will fatal."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/NNC/ModelBuilder/compile